Put Default Image

Create a default image inside public folder

public/images/default.png

Example:

public/images/user.png
2️⃣ Blade File (Display Image)

In your users list / profile blade

<img src="{{ $user->image ? asset('uploads/'.$user->image) : asset('images/default.png') }}" width="80">
Logic
if user image exists
    show uploaded image
else
    show default image
3️⃣ Example Output
Case 1 – Image Uploaded

DB:

image = user1.jpg

Output:

uploads/user1.jpg
Case 2 – Image Not Uploaded

DB:

image = null

Output:

images/default.png
4️⃣ Alternative (More Safe Method)
<img src="{{ asset('uploads/'.$user->image) }}" 
     onerror="this.src='{{ asset('images/default.png') }}'" 
     width="80">

This will also show default image if file is missing.
